&lt;p&gt;The Luton and Dunstable University Hospital is committed to excellence and to the provision of high quality healthcare. We want to be one of the safest hospitals in the country and our patient’s safety is our priority. We have successfully implemented an electronic prescribing and administration system across all inpatient areas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic pharmacy technician to work as a key part of the pharmacy team within our modern automated, dispensary and distribution area and back stores. You will be supervising staff in day to day activities and training staff. Alongside you will be supporting the Senior Pharmacy Technician Distribution, Stores &amp; QA with stock management, processes and standards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must be able to demonstrate an enthusiasm for trying new roles, supporting innovation and delivering an excellent patient experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: 1.35em;&quot;&gt;Please contact Principal Pharmacy Technician, Dispensary, Distribution and Stores Manager, Lianne Eldridge on 01582 497365 or Prafula Patel Senior Pharmacy Technician Distribution, Stores &amp; QA on 01582 497368.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
